Please help me refactor this React Class component into a Functional Component:

class Counter extends React.Component {
  state = { count: 0 };
  increment = () => {
    this.setState({ count: this.state.count + 1 });
  };
  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <p>{this.state.count}</p>
        <button onClick={this.increment}>Increment</button>
      </div>
    );
  }
}

Here's the code refactoring your Counter class component into a functional component using the useState Hook:

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const Counter: React.FC = () => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  const increment = () => {
    setCount(count + 1);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <p>{count}</p>
      <button onClick={increment}>Increment</button>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Counter;
```

You can use the useEffect Hook to simulate componentDidMount by passing an empty dependency array:

```tsx
import React, { useEffect } from 'react';

const MyComponent: React.FC = () => {
  useEffect(() => {
    // componentDidMount logic
    console.log('Component mounted');
  }, []); // Empty array ensures it runs only once on mount

  return <div>Example Component</div>;
};

export default MyComponent;
```

能帮我把下面这个复杂的 Class 组件也重构成 FC 组件吗？

class TodoList extends React.Component {
  state = { todos: [] };
  componentDidMount() {
    fetch('/api/todos')
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => this.setState({ todos: data }));
  }
  render() {
    return (
      <ul>
        {this.state.todos.map(todo => (
          <li key={todo.id}>{todo.text}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    );
  }
}

Certainly! Here's the refactored version as a functional component:

```tsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

type Todo = { id: number; text: string };

const TodoList: React.FC = () => {
  const [todos, setTodos] = useState<Todo[]>([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/todos')
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => setTodos(data));
  }, []);

  return (
    <ul>
      {todos.map(todo => (
        <li key={todo.id}>{todo.text}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
};

export default TodoList;
```
